Well, I'm paying them
enough to plug their ears!

19:59.680 --> 20:02.411
God damn it. You're drunk!
I want to go back inside.

20:03.000 --> 20:04.968
You're not going anywhere.

20:07.160 --> 20:09.640
Bitch! Did you just hit me?
Is that what you did?

20:11.080 --> 20:12.411
You don't ever hit me!

20:12.560 --> 20:13.891
Bitch!

20:14.840 --> 20:16.080
I'm sorry!

20:16.160 --> 20:18.128
Don't ever hit Charlie!

20:18.760 --> 20:20.683
Do you understand that?

20:21.320 --> 20:23.163
Remember where you come from.

20:23.280 --> 20:25.089
Remember, you bitch!

22:35.000 --> 22:36.047
Miss?

22:41.440 --> 22:42.601
Help me.

22:45.280 --> 22:46.406
Please.

22:48.160 --> 22:49.605
Do I call 911?

22:50.000 --> 22:51.126
No.

22:51.600 --> 22:53.807
I don't want him to go to jail.

23:42.600 --> 23:44.887
You have to stand up. Stand up!

23:46.480 --> 23:47.845
Help me. Stand up!

24:04.880 --> 24:05.881
Shh.

24:15.840 --> 24:16.841
It's okay.

24:18.080 --> 24:19.081
Be quiet.

24:24.360 --> 24:25.600
Lillian. Shh.

24:26.000 --> 24:27.240
Just don't let him in.

24:27.320 --> 24:28.481
It's Charlie.

24:30.000 --> 24:31.286
I'm sorry.

24:31.560 --> 24:33.528
Please just open the door.

24:36.960 --> 24:39.691
Come on, I'm sorry.
Let's just talk about this

24:41.840 --> 24:43.046
Lillian!

24:43.760 --> 24:45.250
Shit. Please...

24:45.320 --> 24:46.765
Lillian, open the door.

24:49.440 --> 24:51.204
Open the fucking door!

25:11.080 --> 25:12.081
Oh, great.

25:16.520 --> 25:18.648
Mmm. Mmm.

25:20.040 --> 25:21.326
Thank you.

25:22.480 --> 25:24.721
I'm sorry. I'm really sorry.

25:25.800 --> 25:27.211
What are you sorry for?

25:27.280 --> 25:30.443
I'm just sorry because
you're involved now in this.

25:31.880 --> 25:34.360
And I didn't mean
for this to happen.

25:35.200 --> 25:37.202
Well, you needn't be sorry.

25:41.000 --> 25:45.562
He works so hard and when he works,
he sometimes gets stressed

25:45.640 --> 25:48.803
and when he's under a lot of
pressure, he drinks a lot.

25:48.880 --> 25:52.407
And I think I set him off,
and I don't mean to.

25:53.160 --> 25:54.605
I feel so bad.

25:55.640 --> 25:57.802
Why are you making
excuses for him?

25:57.880 --> 26:00.963
'Cause you really don't know him.
He's a really, um...

26:05.160 --> 26:06.810
Reliable guy.

26:06.880 --> 26:08.609
Stop apologizing for him.

26:09.720 --> 26:10.767
Stop it.

26:12.040 --> 26:13.485
I do love him.

26:30.920 --> 26:33.161
Why would someone
kill a violinist?

26:33.240 --> 26:35.641
This job really sucks sometimes.

26:35.720 --> 26:39.008
Why would an 80-year-old woman
wanna jump off her balcony?

26:39.080 --> 26:42.289
See this here?
This is how I like my crime scene.

26:42.360 --> 26:44.727
That over there is
a torso, a head,

26:46.160 --> 26:47.491
and right down here...

26:47.560 --> 26:48.686
Oh, God.

26:48.760 --> 26:49.807
What the hell is that?

26:50.360 --> 26:52.249
You see, this is what a
murder scene looks like.

26:52.400 --> 26:54.880
What, so you don't think
this is a suicide as well?

26:57.400 --> 26:59.289
You, my friend, are
a sick bastard.

26:59.360 --> 27:00.407
I'm just saying,

27:00.480 --> 27:02.244
nine years on the job,
it just doesn't add up.

27:02.320 --> 27:05.324
What's interesting is the
girl across the hall.

27:05.800 --> 27:07.689
Oh, I see what this is about.

27:07.760 --> 27:09.091
What, she's hot?

27:09.160 --> 27:10.605
Yeah, she was attractive.
I knew it.

27:10.680 --> 27:11.841
No, here's the thing.

27:11.920 --> 27:14.002
- I ran her through the system, right?
- Please.

27:14.080 --> 27:16.447
There's nothing on her.
She doesn't have a social security number.

27:16.520 --> 27:18.284
She doesn't have a
driver's license, nothing.

27:18.960 --> 27:22.203
A woman like that, living in Columbus
Circle, with all that money?

27:22.280 --> 27:24.328
It just doesn't make sense.

27:24.840 --> 27:27.810
You know, she hasn't left
her apartment in years.

27:27.880 --> 27:30.724
This is New York City.
It's a town full of nuts.

27:30.800 --> 27:32.768
No, she didn't look crazy.

27:33.560 --> 27:35.130
How did she look?

27:36.240 --> 27:38.163
She looked like a victim.

28:24.440 --> 28:25.487
Mmm...

28:30.440 --> 28:31.771
Oh, my God.

28:34.480 --> 28:36.323
I can't believe I
fell asleep here.

28:43.280 --> 28:44.441
What time is it?

28:45.680 --> 28:47.284
It's almost 8:30.

28:47.720 --> 28:48.767
Oh, wow.

28:49.720 --> 28:52.371
Almost nine hours. Oh, my God.

28:54.840 --> 28:57.161
I'm sorry if I
invaded your space.

28:58.600 --> 29:00.045
It's all right.

29:00.720 --> 29:02.210
Would you like me to
pour you some tea?

29:02.280 --> 29:04.089
No, no, no, that's okay.
I just...

29:04.160 --> 29:06.766
I need to get going.
Thank you, though.

29:07.600 --> 29:09.568
Oh, God, Charlie's
gonna kill me.

29:09.720 --> 29:13.008
It looks like he already
tried to do that last night.

29:13.520 --> 29:14.601
Does it look bad?

29:17.920 --> 29:19.081
Do you have a mirror?

29:22.000 --> 29:23.570
It's right there.

29:32.760 --> 29:33.807
Oh...

29:50.400 --> 29:51.970
I feel so stupid.

29:53.000 --> 29:54.001
No.

29:55.760 --> 29:57.808
I do. I just feel so stupid.

30:00.600 --> 30:02.329
I don't even know you

30:02.920 --> 30:05.400
and here I am dragging
you into this.

30:06.880 --> 30:08.120
It's all right.

30:08.200 --> 30:09.247
God.

30:13.960 --> 30:15.530
It's all right. Don't. Don't.

30:19.240 --> 30:21.083
Why don't you sit down?

30:23.440 --> 30:25.283
I'll pour you some tea.

30:32.680 --> 30:33.966
Thank you.

30:35.080 --> 30:36.764
You've been so nice.

30:42.680 --> 30:43.727
I'm sorry.

30:45.880 --> 30:48.042
Charlie's not such a bad guy.

30:48.480 --> 30:49.845
I don't want you to hate him.

30:51.120 --> 30:53.122
Well, he made a terrible
first impression.

30:53.200 --> 30:54.281
I know.

30:54.840 --> 30:56.001
He did.

31:04.720 --> 31:06.290
Can I ask you a question?

31:09.320 --> 31:11.607
Why don't you like
having any visitors?

31:13.280 --> 31:15.760
I'm sorry, I don't mean to pry.

31:15.840 --> 31:18.446
That's what the real
estate agent said.

31:22.000 --> 31:26.642
Well, I guess I just decided a long
time ago that I'd rather be alone.

31:26.720 --> 31:28.609
That's not so strange.

31:28.840 --> 31:31.047
Sometimes I just wanna run away

31:33.360 --> 31:37.922
and be somewhere where nobody knows
me and I could just start over.

31:46.240 --> 31:47.401
I know.

31:49.120 --> 31:50.281
So what did you do?

31:50.400 --> 31:52.448
<i>I told you. He was coming back.</i>

31:52.800 --> 31:56.600
So I went out into the hallway
and I brought her in.

31:56.680 --> 31:59.001
The hall?
You went into the hall?

31:59.080 --> 32:01.082
<i>You know, she reminded me of...</i>

32:01.760 --> 32:04.366
Well, you know, you were there.
And...

32:04.880 --> 32:06.450
Well, I was...

32:07.520 --> 32:09.648
I was just a child then and,

32:11.880 --> 32:14.406
well, I wasn’t gonna
just stand there

32:14.960 --> 32:16.371
and watch this happen.

32:16.440 --> 32:18.124
So you called the
police, of course.

32:20.360 --> 32:21.361
No.

32:22.080 --> 32:23.241
What happened?

32:25.880 --> 32:27.405
Well, when she woke
up this morning...

32:27.480 --> 32:29.482
<i>"When she woke up”?
You mean she slept over?"</i>

32:29.680 --> 32:32.001
Well, it was hardly a
slumber party, Ray.

32:32.080 --> 32:33.889
She was injured

32:34.560 --> 32:36.050
and she passed out.

32:36.760 --> 32:37.807
What's her name?

32:40.200 --> 32:41.201
Lillian.

32:42.920 --> 32:44.570
<i>Is she still there?</i>

32:47.240 --> 32:48.241
No.

32:48.840 --> 32:50.046
She left.

32:51.120 --> 32:52.451
<i>She gonna be safe there?</i>

32:57.080 --> 32:58.206
I don't know.

32:58.280 --> 32:59.486
<i>Oh, Abby.</i>

33:00.200 --> 33:02.043
<i>What are you gonna do now?</i>

33:02.120 --> 33:05.408
<i>You know as well as anyone this
sort of thing only gets worse.</i>

33:05.480 --> 33:08.529
I don't know.
It's not my responsibility, right?

33:08.600 --> 33:10.523
Maybe you should consider that
now that you've helped her

33:10.600 --> 33:12.489
she'll likely come back
to you for help again.

33:12.560 --> 33:14.767
<i>Have you thought about what
you're gonna do next time?</i>

33:14.840 --> 33:15.841
No.

33:15.960 --> 33:16.961
Gimme a mini. Yeah.

33:17.040 --> 33:18.087
Schmear?

33:18.640 --> 33:21.007
I just know I don't
wanna be involved.

33:21.080 --> 33:22.241
<i>It's a little late for that.</i>

33:22.520 --> 33:26.081
And Abigail, it's unfair for you
to give her refuge and solace

33:26.160 --> 33:28.561
<i>and then when she comes
knocking again to ignore her.</i>

33:28.640 --> 33:31.928
<i>Maybe you could be proactive
and talk to her, help her.</i>

33:32.000 --> 33:33.490
I don't know.

33:33.560 --> 33:36.166
<i>Well, it's something to consider.
She's your neighbor.</i>

33:36.240 --> 33:37.526
<i>You have something in common.</i>

33:37.720 --> 33:39.802
Maybe you should have her for
dinner, over to your place.

33:39.880 --> 33:43.202
I don't think I'm entirely
comfortable with that idea, Ray.

33:43.400 --> 33:44.401
Think about it.

33:44.480 --> 33:45.481
All right.

33:47.160 --> 33:49.208
Are you eating? Yeah.

33:49.280 --> 33:51.089
Bagel with a schmear. Bye.

34:13.840 --> 34:15.728
You really banged me up.

34:18.000 --> 34:19.286
I'm sorry.

34:20.560 --> 34:21.846
<i>I mean it</i>

34:23.560 --> 34:24.891
I love you.

34:26.560 --> 34:27.925
I love you.

34:42.320 --> 34:43.650
Thank you, Bubba.

34:43.719 --> 34:45.210
You're welcome, Miss Hart.

34:47.239 --> 34:48.889
Miss Lillian, can I help
you with that, please?

34:49.400 --> 34:50.925
I'm sorry! I'm terribly sorry!
Oh, wait.

34:51.000 --> 34:53.367
I've got it. No, don't, wait.

34:53.440 --> 34:55.726
You having fun down
there, Klandermann?

34:55.800 --> 34:58.087
No, sir. No, sir, not at all.
I was just trying to help with...

34:58.160 --> 34:59.207
I'm kidding, I'm kidding.
Let me help.

34:59.280 --> 35:00.281
Oh, good.

35:00.360 --> 35:02.124
This... I shouldn't see that.

35:02.200 --> 35:04.328
It's fine. Okay. All right.
I'll get the elevator.

35:07.040 --> 35:08.201
There we are.

35:08.280 --> 35:09.805
I'm so sorry.
I was trying to help.

35:09.880 --> 35:11.291
Don't worry about it.
There were just so many bags.

35:11.360 --> 35:12.486
I didn't realize... It's fine.

35:12.560 --> 35:15.370
It's not all for me.
I bought you a new tie.

35:15.760 --> 35:17.046
A new tie?

35:19.880 --> 35:21.609
A new tie? Yeah A new tie.

35:24.080 --> 35:25.127
Right here, sir?

35:25.640 --> 35:26.880
On the counter, please. Uh-huh.

35:27.120 --> 35:28.167
Excuse me, sorry.

35:28.240 --> 35:29.241
Thank you.

35:38.360 --> 35:39.805
Everything all right,
Klandermann?

35:39.880 --> 35:41.245
Yeah. Yeah, yeah.

35:41.320 --> 35:42.526
Well, no.

35:43.000 --> 35:44.240
That's...

35:44.440 --> 35:45.487
That's where I found her.

35:46.840 --> 35:48.330
Found who?

35:48.400 --> 35:49.845
Mrs.
Lonnigan, the previous tenant.

35:50.880 --> 35:52.166
What do you mean?
Well, that's...

35:52.240 --> 35:54.402
I was the one that found her.
Right here.

35:56.000 --> 35:58.731
They said she fell
down the stairs.

35:59.520 --> 36:01.124
I didn't know that.

36:01.200 --> 36:02.884
She was such a sweet old
lady, too, you know?

36:02.960 --> 36:04.200
Everybody loved her
in the building.

36:04.800 --> 36:06.370
Always had something
sweet to say

36:06.440 --> 36:07.965
and always made everybody smile.

36:08.040 --> 36:09.565
The whole building
loved her, really.

36:09.640 --> 36:11.130
That's so sad.

36:11.200 --> 36:13.202
I'd just never seen
anybody die before.

36:15.080 --> 36:16.161
What do you mean?

36:16.400 --> 36:20.086
She wasn't dead yet
when I found her. No.

36:20.160 --> 36:23.130
We got a call, the tenant
down below, Henderson,

36:23.640 --> 36:24.971
they heard a real loud...

36:25.040 --> 36:27.850
And I raced to...
And the door was unlocked,

36:27.920 --> 36:32.209
which is quite unusual for a building
like this, I'll tell you that.

36:32.280 --> 36:35.443
But it seemed as if she
were still trying to speak.

36:36.200 --> 36:37.725
What was she trying to say?

36:37.800 --> 36:39.245
Oh, I have no idea.

36:39.600 --> 36:41.728
See, I'd never seen
anything and there she...

36:41.800 --> 36:45.441
It was awful, so it's all
kind of a blur now, you know.

36:46.440 --> 36:48.329
Yeah. Yeah, that's a shame.

36:48.400 --> 36:50.641
I mean, I have an idea
I shouldn't say that.

36:50.720 --> 36:52.609
I haven't told anybody this
before, but when I found her

36:52.680 --> 36:56.890
it sounded like she was
trying to say, uh, "Why?"

36:57.560 --> 36:58.721
"Why?"

36:58.800 --> 37:00.404
But it was a "Why me?"

37:00.480 --> 37:03.131
"Why did this happen to me?"
kind of "why." Does that make

37:05.360 --> 37:06.691
any, uh...

37:10.480 --> 37:12.289
I'm so sorry.
I should not be here.

37:12.360 --> 37:14.089
I'm so sorry to
take up your time.

37:14.160 --> 37:17.004
Do you need any help unloading
these bags at all or...

37:17.080 --> 37:18.650
I'll remember how I
know you, Mr. Stanford.

37:18.720 --> 37:20.245
I swear I will.
I'm so sorry I haven't.

37:20.480 --> 37:21.561
All right, let me
know when you do.

37:21.640 --> 37:22.641
Sure thing.

37:25.840 --> 37:27.524
What was that about?

37:28.160 --> 37:29.969
He thinks he knows me.

37:30.800 --> 37:32.165
Does he?

37:32.240 --> 37:33.321
I don't think so.

38:00.600 --> 38:01.601
Hi. Sorry.

38:01.680 --> 38:03.284
This, um... From...

38:04.400 --> 38:05.401
You're good?

38:06.200 --> 38:07.725
Thank you. Okay.

38:24.440 --> 38:27.887
Before you moved around, you were
just in Bakersfield that whole time?

38:27.960 --> 38:29.450
Bakersfield, California.

38:29.520 --> 38:33.320
My mom drank, mostly to
get away from my father,

38:33.760 --> 38:36.001
who also drank.

38:38.040 --> 38:39.041
Hmm.

38:39.120 --> 38:40.963
Was he abusive? Yeah.

38:41.040 --> 38:43.042
That's pretty much why I left,

38:43.880 --> 38:46.565
because I couldn't take it any more.
I was 15

38:47.760 --> 38:50.525
and I had $7.20 to my name.

38:51.600 --> 38:53.762
And I had fallen in
love with Charlie

38:54.680 --> 38:57.843
and he's pretty much
just taken care of me.

38:58.800 --> 39:00.484
I couldn't...

39:00.560 --> 39:02.608
I couldn't stay with
someone who hurt me.

39:02.680 --> 39:05.809
I mean, we have a good time,
but I don't really...

39:07.080 --> 39:09.890
I wouldn't really have
anything without him

39:12.240 --> 39:13.651
I just couldn't do it.

39:14.080 --> 39:15.684
So what's the alternative?

39:20.480 --> 39:21.561
Would you like some more wine?

39:21.640 --> 39:23.290
Yes, please.

39:28.280 --> 39:29.930
So where's your family?

39:30.000 --> 39:31.331
My mom died.

39:31.840 --> 39:33.046
And your father?

39:34.760 --> 39:36.250
He's dead, too.

39:36.360 --> 39:37.407
Oh.

39:37.520 --> 39:39.443
Were you close with them?

39:40.480 --> 39:42.005
I was close with my mother.

39:42.640 --> 39:43.721
Mmm-hmm.

39:44.080 --> 39:45.286
My dad...

39:45.360 --> 39:47.249
My dad drank as well

39:47.320 --> 39:50.483
and he'd fly off the handle.
He'd go into these rages.

39:52.160 --> 39:54.049
And he would beat
my mother and me

39:55.280 --> 39:56.566
when I tried to protect her.

39:58.480 --> 39:59.606
Mmm-hmm.

40:01.680 --> 40:02.681
Hmm.

40:02.760 --> 40:05.047
My father could
control anything.

40:10.960 --> 40:12.644
So you grew up rich?

40:18.160 --> 40:19.366
I suppose.

40:19.440 --> 40:21.522
Well, I grew up in
the trailer park.

40:24.680 --> 40:25.886
Lucky me.

40:27.600 --> 40:29.204
Do you have any
brothers or sisters?

40:29.280 --> 40:30.327
Nope.

40:31.080 --> 40:32.127
Just me.

40:32.800 --> 40:34.609
You? No. Just me, too.

40:36.120 --> 40:37.451
So how'd you disappear?

40:40.160 --> 40:41.844
Haven't I always
been there for you?

40:42.240 --> 40:43.287
My father had a friend.

40:43.360 --> 40:46.443
My father had a friend and he
knew how bad my father could be

40:46.520 --> 40:49.729
and what he was capable
of, so he helped me to...

40:49.800 --> 40:50.881
He helped me.

40:51.840 --> 40:53.490
You know, I didn't
intentionally...

40:53.560 --> 40:55.085
I didn't set out intentionally.

40:55.160 --> 40:59.484
To not go out again. I just...

41:00.160 --> 41:02.640
You know, I went to
the grocery store

41:03.120 --> 41:05.566
<i>and I'd sneak out at night,</i>

41:07.080 --> 41:08.366
go to Central Park.

41:09.400 --> 41:13.246
<i>I was always amazed at how
quiet everything was.</i>

41:13.800 --> 41:15.689
Such a big city.

41:17.440 --> 41:18.965
I wanna take you outside.

41:20.040 --> 41:22.486
There's this flower shop.
It's a block away.

41:23.400 --> 41:25.084
I wanna take you there.

41:25.160 --> 41:26.650
It smells so incredible

41:27.640 --> 41:29.688
and I wanna pick out
your favorite flowers.

41:29.960 --> 41:33.169
And then a block further
is this rare bookstore

41:33.240 --> 41:37.086
that smells kind of musky and it
has the most incredible books,

41:37.160 --> 41:39.970
and there's this window seating
and we can pick out some books

41:40.040 --> 41:41.804
and read together.

41:42.760 --> 41:44.649
I don't think I'd feel safe.

41:45.080 --> 41:46.286
I would be with you,

41:46.880 --> 41:48.120
protecting you.

41:48.200 --> 41:50.931
You can't stay in here for the
rest of your life. Look at you.

41:51.240 --> 41:52.924
You're so beautiful.

41:57.400 --> 41:58.447
<i>You're stunning.</i>

41:59.840 --> 42:01.569
I wanna take you out
into the world.

42:14.400 --> 42:16.209
You smell his lavender?

42:17.360 --> 42:19.727
Let's see if he's
in the backyard.

42:20.840 --> 42:23.844
This is a nice house.
I should've been a doctor.

42:24.360 --> 42:25.361
Hello?

42:28.000 --> 42:29.525
You smell paint?

42:31.560 --> 42:34.211
Oh, for Christ's sake.

42:34.280 --> 42:37.011
My good shoes.
My mom's gonna have a fit.

42:37.320 --> 42:39.243
I just painted that porch.

42:39.480 --> 42:42.051
I'm so sorry.

42:42.560 --> 42:44.608
We had no idea.

42:45.880 --> 42:48.884
I'm so sorry.
You must be Dr. Ray Fontaine?

42:49.080 --> 42:50.206
Yes.

42:50.280 --> 42:51.805
Yeah, I'm Detective
Frank Giardello.

42:51.880 --> 42:53.086
This is my partner, Jerry Eaans.

42:53.160 --> 42:56.130
Two detectives and you couldn't figure
out the porch was freshly painted?

42:56.600 --> 42:58.364
We're really sorry.

42:58.440 --> 43:01.410
We were wondering if we could
